-- ADB raises $50 mln via offshore rupee-linked bonds - statement
-- By Rajesh Kumar Singh
-- Tue Aug 26, 2014 01:57AM EDT
-- None



NEW DELHI, Aug 26 (Reuters) - The Asian Development Bank has raised $50 million through offshore, Indian rupee-linked, the lender said in a statement on Tuesday.

The rupee-denominated bonds would be settled in US dollars and would mature in August 2016, the statement said.